President Obama expresses his admiration for the life of Blessed Damien de Veuster, who is being canonized by Pope Benedict XVI. He acknowledges the pride of the Kingdom of Belgium and its people in having Fr. Damien as one of their citizens. The President also highlights Fr. Damien's significance to Hawaiians, recalling his tireless work in caring for those suffering from leprosy. He emphasizes that Fr. Damien challenged the stigma surrounding the disease and sacrificed his own life to bring dignity to those affected. President Obama encourages drawing inspiration from Fr. Damien's example in addressing the global health challenges of our time, particularly the HIV/AIDS pandemic. He offers his prayers and joins people of all faiths in celebrating Fr. Damien's extraordinary life and witness.